QUESTION 572f55e8a23a5019007fc56c = What is the French name for the Rhine? 
   
TEXT 572f55e8a23a5019007fc56c = [note 3] The spelling with Rh- in English Rhine as well as in German Rhein and French Rhin is due to the influence of Greek orthography, while the vocalisation -i- is due to the Proto-Germanic adoption of the Gaulish name as *Rnaz, via Old Frankish giving Old English Rn, Old High German Rn, Dutch Rijn (formerly also spelled Rhijn)).
